==English==

===Etymology===
First attested around 1425. From {{etyl|frm|en}} {{term|absorber|lang=frm}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|assorbir|lang=fro}},from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|absorbeō||swallow up}}, from {{term|ab||from|lang=la}} + {{m|la|sorbeō||suck in, swallow}}; akin to {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|ῥοφέω|tr=ropheō||sup up|lang=grc}}, {{etyl|mga|-}} {{term|srub||snout|lang=mga}}, {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|srebti|srēbti|to sip|lang=lt}}, and perhaps to {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|surpfeln|sürpfeln|to sip|lang=gmh}}, and {{etyl|no|-}} {{term|slurpe|lang=no}}. Compare French {{term|absorber|lang=fr}}.

