===Verb===
{{en-verb|absorbs|absorbing|absorbed|past2=absorpt|past2_qual=archaic}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[include]] so that it no longer has [[separate]] existence; to [[overwhelm]]; to cause to [[disappear]] as if by [[swallowing]] up; to [[incorporate]]; to [[assimilate]]; to take in and [[use up]]. {{defdate|First attested around 1350 to 1470.}}<ref name=SOED>{{reference-book|editor=Brown, Lesley|title=The Shorter Oxford English Dictionary|origdate= |origyear=1933|origmonth= |edition=5th|date=|year=2003|month=|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford, UK|language=|isbn=978-0-19-860575-7|pages=9|chapter=|quote=}}</ref>
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:William Cowper|William Cowper]]:
#*: Dark oblivion soon '''absorbs''' them all.
#* {{rfdate}} [[w:Washington Irving|Washington Irving]]:
#*: The large cities '''absorb''' the wealth and fashion.
# {{context|transitive|obsolete|lang=en}} To engulf, as in water; to [[swallow up]]. {{defdate|Attested from the late 15<sup>th</sup> century until the late 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-book|year=1879|author={{w|Thomas Burnet}}|title=The Sacred Theory of the Earth||passage=to be '''absorpt''', or swallowed up, in a lake of fire and brimstone.}}
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[suck up]]; to [[drink in]]; to [[imbibe]]; as a [[sponge]] or as the [[lacteals]] of the body; to chemically take in. {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive|physics|chemistry|lang=en}} To take in energy and convert it, as{{defdate|First attested in the early 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
## {{context|transitive|physics|lang=en}} in receiving a physical impact or vibration without recoil.
## {{context|transitive|physics|lang=en}} in receiving sound energy without repercussion or echo.
## {{context|transitive|physics|lang=en}} taking in [[radiant energy]] and converting it to a different form of energy, like heat.
#: ''Heat, light, and electricity are '''absorbed''' in the substances into which they pass.''
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[engross]] or [[engage]] wholly; to [[occupy]] fully; as, '''absorbed''' in study or in the [[pursuit]] of wealth. {{defdate|First attested in the late 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To occupy or consume time. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} Assimilate mentally. {{defdate|First attested in the late 19<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
# {{context|transitive|business|lang=en}} To assume or pay for as part of a [[commercial]] [[transaction]].
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[defray]] the costs.
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To accept or purchase in quantity.

